  "response": "Money laundering generally involves financial transactions intended to conceal the origin of illegally obtained money. Legal definitions typically include three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's source\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into the legitimate economy\n\nSpecific definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but most involve intentionally concealing or disguising the source of criminally derived proceeds.",
